StoreBelow is a bit of about our mission/concept of repurposing.First off, what are some examples of repurposing? It is taking a byproduct or waste stream such as a retired street sweeper brush and giving it a 2nd life as a back scratcher for horses or cattle. It is taking a decommissioned fire hose and giving it an extended life as a boat dock fender. It is taking an obsolete ski lift cable and giving it a second life as hand railing in a luxury condo building. In your efforts to reach Zero Waste, do you have any byproducts or waste from projects now, or coming up, that would be a candidate for repurposing? fix up.name: 2003 Acura CL-S Type, Low Miles, Upgrades, Clean Title, Carfax
fix up.where: hercules, pinole, san pablo, el sob
fix up.description: 2003 Acura CL S-Type130K Original MilesSecond OwnerVtec V6 280horsepower / 5spd AutoHigh performance upgradesUpgraded TransmissionFully servicedCustom stereoClean CarfaxFresh smog and tags are good to September. Title is in hand, and in my namePlease read whole ad before calling, as many questions can be answered belowClean Carfax Shows:No accidents, 2 owner, Clean Title, accurate mileage20 service records from Acura of Stockton from original owner. The original transmissions went out at 100k. However a 2006/2007 Honda Accord V6 uses the same exact trans, except Honda fixed the fatal flaw (2/3rd gear clutch pack oiling) and they are very dependable. I installed a trans out of a 2007 accord that was 1 owner from Dublin, always maintained at Honda with also 100K on the odometer (came out of a salvaged crash car was hit in rear) This trans should last the life of the car without issue. This is a common swap among CL and TL enthusiasts.Along with trans, around 100K I installed a Genuine  Acura Timing belt and water pump kit with tensioner and seals.  All Factory parts. I also did factory Iridium spark plugs and checked the valve adjustment at that time.All 4 brakes are done recently with e-coated rotors, stoptech pads and flushed performance brake fluid2 new motor mounts, Factory AcuraCoolant replaced and power steering fluid flushed with Honda fluidNew HID Ballasts and bulbsNow for the goodies $$*Koni Yellow Rebound adjustable Struts at all 4 corners with stock springs at 1 lower height *Eibach Sway Bars front and rear with poly bushings* All 4 sway bar end links replaced with HD Moog greasable units*Poly strut rod mounts*Real Deal Comptech Stainless Mufflers and Y pipe (can be showroom polished if wanted)*Air sound/restrictor removed from air box (still smog legal no issue, just throatier sound)*Has TL rims on it as opposed to the factory CL rims which look almost identical except the CL rims get curbed easier and don't have the nice dark metallic background color. *Interior has been double dyna-matted (sound deadening) all along back seat area, both doors completely, trunk *Has custom stereo with a 10 Sub with a JL amp powering it, and a 4 channel rockford fosgate powering door speakers and 6x9s, all quality cables throughout even all the way up to the door speakers*Ceramic 20% tinted windows all the way around, nice privacy but  not so dark can't see out and they are the heat resistant pricey ceramicThis CL Runs and Drives excellent, super clean and tasteful. Handles on rails, super comfortable, and plenty of power along with good gas mileage. Everything works, AC cold, both heated seats work, windows, locks, power seats, everything. The negatives:The air bag recall needs to be done, and the seatbelt receiver replaced (both will be done for free at the dealer, I just never got around to it because its a few cities away)Dings on body (see passenger door) and minor visual defects on exterior (rock chips front bumper) 20 year old black car, its super clean and representable but its also not a complete garage queen.Will need tires soon. The current ones will get you where you need to go but theyre at the end of their life.*Price is absolutely firm, no rush to sell, if you like what you see and read you won't be wasting your time coming to see and but this clean machine.*Cody

I bought it almost completely stock other than wheels.I have babied the car my whole ownership never driven hard no CEL Mods Exterior Wheels-Tenzo R Wheels front-19/9 rear-19/10Tires- Hankook Evo 12`s all the way around Front-19/9/255ZR Rear-19/10/295ZR about 10,000 miles oldDrilled and Slotted rotorsN4 Style Fiberglass rear bumper professionally installed at Anderson Behel body shopFront Chin spoiler Black Door handles(more of a replacement but went with flow of car better)Mods PerformanceExhaust-Topspeed(with the custom intake setup sounds great not too loud but very noticable)Custom Intake setup (will explain in person runs great sounds great, still have stock box and am running stock z tube)Motordyne Plenum spacer 5/16Mods Interior Kentwood double din stereoNew speakers all aroundLeather seat coversPulled and repainted center console to fix Nissans plastic based paint looks better and way more durableMishimoto weighted shift knobRed shift bootI have a digital rear view but it stopped working all the wiring with backup cam and everything is still intact and operational I will throw the mirror in at no extra cost but may require custom mounting brackets.Maintenance within my ownershipReplaced both front solenoidsClutch replaced less than 15k miles ago (OEM Replacement)Master and slave cylinders done with clutchReplaced Throttle Body less than 5k miles ago (OEM replacement)Replaced door handlesReplaced weather strippingoil always changed full synthetic at 3k mile intervals(Last change done at 140k miles) Trunk struts replaced for hatchDisclaimers Good/BadCar has been involved in one minor fender bender that is reason for the new modified bumper Fixed Via insurance all work and paint done by Anderson Behel Body shopCars Odometer does read at 142,000 miles but is actually lower because of the size of the rims, Stock setup is a 17/18 staggered setup and I am running 19/9 by 19/10 so the miles are clocking as more than motor really has. loud.name: Peavey Special 130 guitar amp
loud.description: Peavey Special 130. Made in the USA 130 watt solid state amp. Loud if demanded. Working fine. The Tolex is very good condition. I do not have the footswitch so I pull the phone jack out of the rear footswitch input jack to actuate the distortion channel. I cleaned all the pots two times from the inside and outside. The push/pull high EQ knob still has a bit of a scratch noise when adjusted. It makes no noise if you are not adjusting it. The two right knobs and grill cloth are not Peavey produced. This is a fairly heavy duty amp. The power transformer is massive. It looks like it is on casters but the wheels are a small dolly that is not part of the sale.  Leave your number with your response and I will call you.

famous.name: Famous FS-1 Soprano Ukulele OBO
famous.description: Pretty little soprano, nice build with super-thin mahogany laminate, but with a sound that will rival most sold-wood ukes. Extremely light, with excellent projection and beautiful resonance. The FS-1 is a Japanese build, identical to the Kiwaya KS-1, but sold only to the Japanese market. This older uke has a Rosewood fingerboard, which you won't find in production any longer...the newer ones are walnut.  Nice, low action and great intonation. Friction tuners. Tiny scratch on the headstock, mark on the first fret - see the photos for detail. One-of-a-kind cloth gig bag included. Reasonable offers are welcome.

famous.name: 1964 Selmer Mark VI Alto Saxophone
famous.description: Do not pass on this instrument, if you are looking at this, then you know the reputation of the Mark VI, and this one is a good example. This would also be a great investment unlike a new sax that would depreciate in value.This sax plays nice and has that tone the Mark VI is famous for. Original finish but does show slight wear, but very nice for it’s age. No dents & the serial numbers do match, and the original case is in very good condition. Please email with any questions.
